* All three blocks receive the editor css via several ways - what i want is a audit that calculates how the styles css are defined on editor. The goal is, when building, to import the style.css of each block into the editor.css and enquee it on the editor. This way every modification made on the main css automatically applies to the on editor, special editor rules on the bottom of the css, that will override specific frontend rules. Then, analyse edit.js that has many inline attributes defined. These attributes should be compared to the editor.css atributes - those who can be added there via css will, and be deleted from the js, while keeping essential values only that dont conflict with the css. Goal: all three blocks work the same way, and editing a css rule in editor becomes simple.
* Accordion animation lags - accordion-content nedds an inner div - check onlinw how we cannot add the animation directly to the container div because it messes up the calculations of the height when opening. Search online in how the height calculation with padding shoud occur and in which div , to achieve a seamless transition
